.TH "DOMMATRIXREADONLY.DOMMATRIXREADONLY" "3JS" "October 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
DOMMatrixReadOnly.DOMMatrixReadOnly \- DOMMatrixReadOnly:
DOMMatrixReadOnly() constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]DOMMatrixReadOnly()\f[B]\f[R] constructor creates a new
\f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly\f[R] object which represents a 4x4 matrix,
suitable for 2D and 3D operations.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new DOMMatrixReadOnly()
new DOMMatrixReadOnly(initString)
new DOMMatrixReadOnly(initArray)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]initString\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string representing a 2D or 3D matrix in CSS \f[CR]matrix()\f[R] or
\f[CR]matrix3d()\f[R] format.
.TP
\f[B]initArray\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An array containing either 6 or 16 numbers in column\-major order.
Other array lengths throw a \f[CR]TypeError\f[R].
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
A 6\-element array is interpreted as the matrix components
\f[CR][m11, m12, m21, m22, m41, m42]\f[R], creating a 2D matrix.
.IP \(bu 2
A 16\-element array is interpreted as the matrix components
\f[CR][m11, m12, m13, m14, m21, m22, m23, m24, m31, m32, m33, m34, m41, m42, m43, m44]\f[R],
creating a 3D matrix.
.PP
If this argument is omitted, an identity matrix is created, i.e.,
equivalent to \f[CR][1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0]\f[R].
.PP
If this argument is provided as a \f[CR]Float32Array\f[R] or
\f[CR]Float64Array\f[R], consider using the more performant static
methods \f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly.fromFloat32Array()\f[R] or
\f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly.fromFloat64Array()\f[R] instead.
.RE
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly\f[R] object.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if the argument is not a string or an array with a length other
than 6 or 16.
.TP
\f[B]SyntaxError\f[R]
Thrown if the string argument is not in a valid CSS \f[CR]matrix()\f[R]
or \f[CR]matrix3d()\f[R] format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Creating a DOMMatrixReadOnly from a string
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] matrixFromString = \f[B]new\f[R] DOMMatrixReadOnly(\(dqmatrix(1, 0, 0, 1, 10, 20)\(dq);
console.log(matrixFromString.toJSON());
\f[I]// Output: {a: 1, b: 0, c: 0, d: 1, e: 10, f: 20}\f[R]
.EE
.SS Creating a DOMMatrixReadOnly from an array
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] matrixFromArray = \f[B]new\f[R] DOMMatrixReadOnly([1, 0, 0, 1, 10, 20]);
console.log(matrixFromArray.toJSON());
\f[I]// Output: {a: 1, b: 0, c: 0, d: 1, e: 10, f: 20}\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly.fromFloat32Array()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly.fromFloat64Array()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]DOMMatrixReadOnly.fromMatrix()\f[R]
